{
  "texts": [
    "We analysed all electrodes and participants with causal and non-causal versions of the ResNet and Swin decoders.",
    "The results in Fig. 4 show similar contributions for the ResNet and Swin models (Supplementary Figs.",
    "8 and 9 describe the noise-level contribution).",
    "The non-causal models show enhanced auditory cortex contributions compared with the causal models, implicating auditory feedback in decoding, and underlying the importance of employing only causal models during speech decoding because neural feedback signals are not available for real-time decoding applications.",
    "Furthermore, across the causal models, both the right and left hemispheres show similar contributions across the sensorimotor cortex, especially on the ventral portion, suggesting the potential feasibility of right-hemisphere neural prosthetics."
  ]
}